cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a two-stage procedure using a hybrid neural network to model the relationship between input features and output, and then detect feature interactions. It also discusses the error of the learning model and how it affects the recovered interactions, which is a common topic in machine learning. Additionally, the paper could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with detecting pairwise interactions in data. The sub-categories of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible as the paper uses neural networks to solve the problem of recovering pairwise interactions.
